{
  "texts": [
    "Establishing common ground and fostering interdisciplinary teamwork is essential to overcome these barriers.",
    "Another significant problem is the vital necessity to monitor the provenance of generated data objects and scientific conclusions from data collection to quality assurance, analysis, modelling, and, finally, publishing [49].",
    "Provenance is especially crucial in supporting scientific conclusions used in policy and management decisions, because field experiments and procedures may be difficult to replicate due to the difficulties of recreating environmental circumstances.",
    "Computer scientists are making significant progress in creating methods to capture evidence information.",
    "Data processing and analysis information that led to a specific set of results may be documented using scripted analytic tools like R and scientific workflow platforms like Kepler and Taverna."
  ]
}